parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Motor mount failure can cause the engine to shift, resulting in a cracked steering fluid pump, leading to power steering system failure.

Corrosion of subframe mounts can cause the subframe to drop, leading to loss of steering control, difficulty shifting gears, and increased risk of accidents.
Failure of body structure can cause the tailgate to open suddenly, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: post that holds the tailgate closed failed
